- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves counting and analyzing the number of empty balanced tetrahedra in a set of points. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper may involve game-theoretic concepts in analyzing the properties of the tetrahedra. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper may involve designing efficient algorithms for counting the number of empty balanced tetrahedra. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may involve analyzing the computational complexity of algorithms for counting the number of empty balanced tetrahedra.
